Articles.Content:
Hello, are there any plans about adding the Real Plume effect to KW rocketry's engines?

Or is there a way to do it manually?

Thank you

If you want to, you can make them yourself and contribute in GitHub. I am working on the soviet engines' real plume effects right now, and it is pretty slow going if you don't have a whole lot of time on your hands.

Here is a guide for getting started. You should also look at existing RealPlume effects for reference, too.

https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B8d75CnONrbmdlh0bkZ6MEdwREE/view

Quick question regarding Universal Storage. It looks like I would need Tweakscale in order to use as the parts have their stock sizes still but when I look at the config files they have the Tweakscale module removed. Some advice about how I can use this in RO would be great. Thanks.

So I just built my self a RO copy of KSP. I included most of the suggested mods and some others. With I little tinkering I seem to have it running stably. Thing is my rockets keep malfunctioning. I'm not sure if it's the base RO or if it's one of the mods. To be clear I don't think it's a bug. It's like their are built in malfunction modes. Some times the engine does not light. Some times it loses power part way through, or goes out, or explodes. I guess that's realistic but it's just turned up way too high. I literally can't get it to fly.

Is there a place that I can turn this down a notch, so that say 1 in 5 rockets would actually function?

Lee

Some times it loses power part way through, or goes out, or explodes. I guess that's realistic but it's just turned up way too high. I literally can't get it to fly.

Is there a place that I can turn this down a notch, so that say 1 in 5 rockets would actually function?

Lee

If you're using remotetech, your rockets are going to lose connection a couple kilometers away from the launch pad and be uncontrollable. Also, if there is no antenna built into your probe core, the rocket won't be controllable at all, even on the ground, causing your engines to not ignite. To fix this, you could make sure to put enough antennas on your ship to control it in orbit, or just uninstall remotetech entirely.

I'm not sure if it's the base RO or if it's one of the mods. To be clear I don't think it's a bug. It's like their are built in malfunction modes. Some times the engine does not light. Some times it loses power part way through, or goes out, or explodes. I guess that's realistic but it's just turned up way too high. I literally can't get it to fly.

Is there a place that I can turn this down a notch, so that say 1 in 5 rockets would actually function?

Lee

That sounds like you are using the RP-0 (career mode) on top of RO. RP-0 in turn has TestFlight as a recommended mod (so it would auto-install if you use CKAN), which is a mod designed to simulate the reliability aspect of spaceflight. The parts become more and more reliable the more you use them.

Now, if career mode is what you want to play, then it is all intended and well. If, however, you want to play sandbox, then it would probably be better to use a separate install without RP-0 and it's recommended mods.

Is there a place that I can turn this down a notch, so that say 1 in 5 rockets would actually function?

Lee

That sounds like you are using the RP-0 (career mode) on top of RO. RP-0 in turn has TestFlight as a recommended mod (so it would auto-install if you use CKAN), which is a mod designed to simulate the reliability aspect of spaceflight. The parts become more and more reliable the more you use them.

Now, if career mode is what you want to play, then it is all intended and well. If, however, you want to play sandbox, then it would probably be better to use a separate install without RP-0 and it's recommended mods.

Hattivat is likely right about the root cause, as I was having the same issue.

There's also the option of staying in career mode simply removing test flight, as I did. I like the idea of the mode, and I was fine with the mean time to failure simulation, but it doesn't have info for all supported engines in RO and working around ignition failure was simply tedious.

On a completely unrelated note: When do you guys think that RO (and RP-0) for v1.0 will be out? I don't mean to pester you about an exact date, I just wanted to know if it would be on the scale of days, weeks, or months so I could determine if I should continue my 0.90 save.

Edited April 28, 2015 by Oksbad
RO KSP 1.0 update compatibility or update?
Compatibility mainly.
RO is heavily dependent upon other things, if they don't update, then RO has to be reconfigured. Of course part mods will have to be redone as well. It will be a slow process.

so im running RO with RP0 and i get a lot of crashes, i figured that this was because i was close to the ram limit however i did some brutal chopping of unnecessary parts (pretty much all the fuel tanks, cut fasa down to a few components and same with KW etc) removed a lot of small mods which add only a very little to the game and overall managed to save just shy of 500mb on ram load.

the problem is the crashes are just as frequent if not more so and the game launch time has gone from 2 minutes to 4 minutes, i have ATM and dds 1x2k textures so i cant save there and im just wondering if you can point me in the direction to reduce the crashes, and help me sort out my install.
"My game crashes" doesn't nothing in the way for anybody to tell you why or how to fix it. Need some logs.
